HEADWORD: co-author
<hw>co-author</hw> <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>to to be an author
of, together with another author or authors; to author jointly with
others.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>to exist together at the same time.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> coexist.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coax</ent>⟦br⟧
